`Effect.raceAll` generalises `Effect.race` to N candidates — the first success completes the program and the others are interrupted.

`Effect.fork(eff)` schedules `eff` on a new fibre and returns immediately with an `Effect<Fiber<A, E>, never, R>`. The parent keeps running; the forked fibre is supervised and can be joined (await its result) or interrupted (cancel it).

```ts
